-- U.S. CFTC preparing rule for high-frequency traders -regulator
-- By Douwe Miedema
-- Tue May 06, 2014 03:19PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, May 6 (Reuters) - The U.S. derivatives markets regulator is preparing a proposed rule for automated trading, a senior regulator said, after earlier asking market participants for insights on a long list of questions.

"I understand that Commission staff is starting to work on a proposed rule," Scott O'Malia, a member of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission, said in a speech.